\begin{MintedVerbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
Now generate realistic but purely synthetic profiles for one target entity.

Target entity:
\PYGZob{}entity\PYGZus{}name\PYGZcb{}

Time\PYGZhy{}series variables for tasks where this target entity is the primary entity are:
\PYGZob{}all\PYGZus{}time\PYGZus{}series\PYGZus{}variables\PYGZcb{}

Please assign \PYGZob{}k\PYGZus{}profiles\PYGZcb{} different profiles to this target entity.

Please return JSON with this schema:
\PYGZob{}
  \PYGZdq{}entity\PYGZus{}name\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}...\PYGZdq{},
  \PYGZdq{}profiles\PYGZdq{}: [
    \PYGZob{}
      \PYGZdq{}profile\PYGZus{}id\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}1\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZdq{}name\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}...\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZdq{}details\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZob{}
        \PYGZdq{}...\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}...\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZcb{}
    \PYGZcb{}
  ]
\PYGZcb{}

Requirements:
\PYG{k}{1.} The profiles must be realistic and detailed enough to sound like plausible real\PYGZhy{}world descriptions for the target entity.
\PYG{k}{2.} The profiles must be purely synthetic. Do not copy or infer any factual background from the input tasks beyond the entity category itself.
\PYG{k}{3.} The profiles must not contain any information that could affect forecasting for any of the listed time\PYGZhy{}series variables, either directly or indirectly.
\PYG{k}{4.} Avoid predictive signals such as events, trends, operations, demand, weather, outages, anomalies, promotions, policies, schedules, maintenance, failures, holidays, traffic shifts, or any other factor that may influence the time series.
\PYG{k}{5.} Keep the profiles as stable background descriptions only, the details should be realistic and just background information will be enough.
\PYG{k}{6.} Generate exactly \PYGZob{}k\PYGZus{}profiles\PYGZcb{} profiles for the target entity.
\PYG{k}{7.} The returned entity\PYGZus{}name must match the target entity exactly.
\PYG{k}{8.} Make sure the name and details are REALISTIC as if they were describing a real\PYGZhy{}world entity, but do not include any information that could be used to predict the time\PYGZhy{}series variables associated with the entity.
\PYG{k}{9.} Only return a JSON object with the specified schema. Do not include any additional text in the response.
\end{MintedVerbatim}
